newsitem.title: UK: NWE jet barge premiums steady, cargoes easier.
newsitem.headline: NWE jet barge premiums steady, cargoes easier.

text.p: Jet fuel prices slid with IPE futures on Wednesday, with barge premiums steady but those for cargoes slightly easier, traders said.
Nov IPE futures ended $5 down at $225.75 on overnight weekly API figures showing a bearish build in distillate stocks in the key U.S. PADD1 district.

A barge was traded at Nov IPE +$33.5, slightly firmer. Cargoes in NWE were Nov IPE +$30/31, down $2 from Tuesday. Some traders expected more material in the next few days after the return from maintenance of the Nerefco refinery, putting pressure on prices.
